@godisrupt Covid over supply, inventory write downs. Just like the rest of the sector. Only right sized inventory this year. Margins finally going in the right direction, through revenues, going into accelerated revenue over the next 3 quarters.

Listen to Calix’s transcript. Fiber service providers are going into a supercycle and rural service providers with BEAD.

Also, commescope $COMM  its Fiber business to $APH, the premium on assets that can build fiber should be worth way more. As Bead and Data center demand absorbs capacity, margins will accrue to all that can produce fiber… which puts $CLFD in a decent position.
